					<head>Kabbalah</head>
					<msContents class="lccn.loc.gov/sh85018546" rend="visible">
						<summary>A kabbalistic treatise by Natan ben Reuven Shapira.</summary>
						<textLang mainLang="he"/>
						<msItem rend="">
							<locus from="1r" to="305v"/>
							<title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Derashot le-parashiyot ha-shavu῾a ule-mo῾adim : al derekh ha-ḳabalah ṿe-al derekh ha-midrash</title>
							<title xml:lang="he">דרשות לפרשיות השבוע ולמועדים : על דרך הקבלה ועל דרך המדרש</title>
							<note>
								<p>The manuscript is incomplete. It consists of kabbalistic homilies on parts of the Pentateuch, partly delivered in connection with festival occasions. Some of the homilies are dated 1663-1664, Reggio. </p>
								<p>An autograph of Natan Shapira, MS Budapest-Kaufmann (Hungarian Academy of Sciences Library) 34, contains similar material, thus it appears that both manuscripts contain works of the same author.</p>
							</note>
							<author>
								<persName xml:lang="en" key="http://viaf.org/viaf/66342902">Shapira, Natan ben Reuven, -1662</persName>
								<persName xml:lang="he" key="http://viaf.org/viaf/66342902">שפירא, נתן בן ראובן דוד</persName>
							</author>
						</msItem>
					</msContents>
